english:
  title: 'Lamenting Spring: Two Poems'
  author: Sung Hyun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Crimson peach and white plum blossom forth as one—
    Every house breathes mist, and none feel poor.
    How I laugh that spring's radiance is not mine,
    Casually given to the young without thought.

    Scattered petals tangle with the falling rain,
    While grass creeping up the steps turns the curtain green.
    Even in sickness, my heart still seeks spring—
    I break a luxuriant branch and place it in a slender vase.
